To correct the code, you need to ensure that you are correctly calculating the Fibonacci sequence and that you are not making any additions that are not part of the sequence. The correct Fibonacci sequence for the first 8 terms (which is what you are trying to calculate) is 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, and 21.

To calculate the 100th term, you can use the following recursive function:

```javascript
function fibonacci(n) {
  if (n <= 1) {
    return n;
  }
  let a = 0, b = 1, c;
  for (let i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
    c = a + b;
    a = b;
    b = c;
  }
  return c;
}
```

You can call this function with the argument 100 to get the 100th term of the Fibonacci sequence:

```javascript
let result = fibonacci(100);
console.log(result);
```

This will output the 100th term of the Fibonacci sequence. To get the remainder when the 100th term is divided by 8, you can use the following code:

```javascript
let result = fibonacci(100) % 8;
console.log(result);
```

